<i>of the spikes out individually</i>

31:41.149 --> 31:43.068
to attach it to the ball head.

31:43.068 --> 31:44.903
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

31:44.903 --> 31:46.238
Nope.

31:46.238 --> 31:49.366
Two bits down,
not taking down a third one.

31:49.366 --> 31:50.742
Weld 'em on.

31:50.742 --> 31:53.620
<i>Move onto plan B:</i>
<i>attach the threads</i>

31:53.620 --> 31:56.206
<i>with just a basic bead weld.</i>

31:56.206 --> 31:57.666
<i>Weld holds.</i>

31:57.666 --> 31:59.876
You actually have no idea
how happy that makes me.

31:59.876 --> 32:03.505
[sparks zapping]

32:03.505 --> 32:04.965
<i>[rock music]</i>

32:04.965 --> 32:06.633
<i>‐ So I'm starting off today</i>

32:06.633 --> 32:08.635
<i>mounting the rest</i>
<i>of the spikes</i>

32:08.635 --> 32:09.928
<i>to the other half of the ball.</i>

32:09.928 --> 32:11.054
To fit up these spikes,

32:11.054 --> 32:12.556
what I'm going to be doing is

32:12.556 --> 32:15.183
<i>putting them through</i>
<i>half of my ball,</i>

32:15.183 --> 32:17.477
heating up the end,
and actually riveting it over

32:17.477 --> 32:19.062
<i>on the inside of the ball.</i>

32:19.062 --> 32:20.981
So these spikes are
gonna go nowhere.

32:20.981 --> 32:22.774
[rubbing and buzzing]

32:22.774 --> 32:23.817
Making progress.

32:23.817 --> 32:25.485
<i>Only 20 hours left</i>

32:25.485 --> 32:26.778
<i>doesn't feel like</i>
<i>a ton of time...</i>

32:26.778 --> 32:28.697
Done with all the spikes.

32:28.697 --> 32:30.907
<i>But I think I'll be able</i>
<i>to get done.</i>

32:30.907 --> 32:33.410
Could definitely do
some damage with this.

32:33.410 --> 32:35.662
<i>[exciting music]</i>

32:35.662 --> 32:38.623
<i>Today I need to attach</i>
<i>the spiked head to the mace.</i>

32:38.623 --> 32:41.126
<i>After that, it's gonna be</i>
<i>working on the guard,</i>

32:41.126 --> 32:42.794
<i>the pommel...</i>

32:42.794 --> 32:44.588
Everything fits.

32:44.588 --> 32:46.631
And I wanna break a few things.

32:46.631 --> 32:48.800
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:48.800 --> 32:51.178
That passed the test
really, really easy.

32:51.178 --> 32:53.305
<i>It was a long, very hard day,</i>

32:53.305 --> 32:55.974
but I'm very happy
with the results.

32:55.974 --> 32:57.475
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:57.475 --> 32:58.560
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

32:58.560 --> 33:00.103
<i>‐ Got a lot done yesterday,</i>

33:00.103 --> 33:02.230
<i>pretty much just gotta do</i>
<i>my handle.</i>

33:02.230 --> 33:03.857
<i>What this project needs is</i>

33:03.857 --> 33:06.651
<i>a khanda‐style</i>
<i>figure eight guard</i>

33:06.651 --> 33:07.694
and a knuckle bow.

33:07.694 --> 33:09.196
That looks frickin' awesome.

33:09.196 --> 33:10.697
<i>I'm really, really pleased</i>

33:10.697 --> 33:12.741
with how that guard turned out.

33:12.741 --> 33:15.160
<i>Typically, I try to make</i>
<i>whatever I'm making</i>

33:15.160 --> 33:16.912
aesthetically pleasing
as possible,

33:16.912 --> 33:19.956
<i>so I've decided to put</i>
<i>some decorative little grooves</i>

33:19.956 --> 33:21.249
<i>in my knuckle bow.</i>

33:21.249 --> 33:23.210
Time to rivet it all together.

33:23.210 --> 33:25.545
<i>I got my knuckle bow</i>
<i>made out of mild steel,</i>

33:25.545 --> 33:28.298
<i>and I'm attaching</i>
<i>with copper rivets,</i>

33:28.298 --> 33:30.717
<i>disc pommel</i>
<i>with a wrought iron cap.</i>

33:30.717 --> 33:32.677
<i>It's as secure</i>
<i>as I could have hoped for.</i>

33:32.677 --> 33:35.430
<i>All I have left to do</i>
<i>is put on a leather wrap,</i>

33:35.430 --> 33:37.849
and this project is a wrap.

33:37.849 --> 33:40.852
[laughs]

33:40.852 --> 33:42.520
<i>[rock music]</i>

33:42.520 --> 33:44.231
<i>‐ The first thing</i>
<i>I'm gonna do today is drill</i>

33:44.231 --> 33:46.066
<i>a hole through the head,</i>
<i>through the shaft,</i>

33:46.066 --> 33:47.359
<i>and out the other side</i>
<i>of the head</i>

33:47.359 --> 33:49.236
<i>in order to pin this head</i>

33:49.236 --> 33:51.112
<i>into place against the shaft.</i>

33:51.112 --> 33:52.906
<i>I've already welded</i>
<i>the head to the shaft,</i>

33:52.906 --> 33:56.201
but I wanna make sure
this ball isn't going anywhere.

33:56.201 --> 33:58.912
That's a spikey murder ball.

33:58.912 --> 34:01.915
<i>[tense music]</i>

34:01.915 --> 34:03.375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:03.375 --> 34:05.293
‐ Jason, Sam,
welcome back to The Forge.

34:05.293 --> 34:07.671
You fellas have had four days
at your home forges

34:07.671 --> 34:09.381
to work on your finale weapons.

34:09.381 --> 34:10.715
It's a very unique weapon.

34:10.715 --> 34:12.050
It's time for you to tell
the judges

34:12.050 --> 34:13.551
about what you've made.

34:13.551 --> 34:14.594
Jason.

34:14.594 --> 34:16.054
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:16.054 --> 34:18.139
<i>‐ I used S7 tool steel</i>
<i>for the head,</i>

34:18.139 --> 34:20.892
<i>mounting to</i>
<i>a mild steel sphere</i>

34:20.892 --> 34:23.979
<i>with 1018 as the shaft</i>
<i>and the guard</i>

34:23.979 --> 34:25.730
<i>and leather‐wrapped</i>
<i>the handle.</i>

34:25.730 --> 34:27.065
‐ All right, all right.

34:27.065 --> 34:28.108
You think it's worthy of
the title

34:28.108 --> 34:29.567
"Forged in Fire" champion?

34:29.567 --> 34:31.111
‐ Absolutely.
It's a spikey murder ball.

34:31.111 --> 34:33.071
‐ All right.
Sam, what do you think?

34:33.071 --> 34:34.614
‐ I'm excited.

34:34.614 --> 34:36.449
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

34:36.449 --> 34:39.452
<i>All the spikes are forged out</i>
<i>of 4140 tool steel.</i>

34:39.452 --> 34:41.538
<i>The ball, shaft, and guard</i>
<i>pieces</i>

34:41.538 --> 34:43.248
<i>are all made out</i>
<i>of mild steel,</i>

34:43.248 --> 34:46.251
<i>and the handle is wrapped</i>
<i>in bark‐tanned deerskin</i>

34:46.251 --> 34:47.961
<i>that I tanned myself.</i>

34:47.961 --> 34:49.254
‐ Well, gentlemen,

34:49.254 --> 34:50.338
your weapons will now be
put through

34:50.338 --> 34:51.381
a series of three tests.

34:51.381 --> 34:52.465
There will be a strength test,

34:52.465 --> 34:53.717
a sharpness test,

34:53.717 --> 34:55.635
and up first, Doug's KEAL test.

34:55.635 --> 34:59.139
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:59.139 --> 35:02.142
All right, bladesmiths,
welcome to the KEAL test.

35:02.142 --> 35:03.351
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:03.351 --> 35:05.186
To find out what kind
of lethal damage

35:05.186 --> 35:06.271
your weapon will do,

35:06.271 --> 35:07.522
I will take your spiked mace

35:07.522 --> 35:08.773
and deliver some killing blows

35:08.773 --> 35:11.776
on this unsuspecting
ballistics dummy.

35:11.776 --> 35:13.028
Jason, you're up first.
You ready for this?

35:13.028 --> 35:14.988
‐ Absolutely.
‐ Let's do this.

35:14.988 --> 35:18.491
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:18.491 --> 35:20.076
<i>‐ I'm expecting for this mace</i>

35:20.076 --> 35:23.496
<i>to absolute destroy this</i>
<i>dummy.</i>

35:23.496 --> 35:25.081
It's gonna be a mess.

35:25.081 --> 35:28.126
<i>[heavy rock music]</i>

35:28.126 --> 35:35.258
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:36.718 --> 35:37.969
‐ [grunts]

35:37.969 --> 35:44.934
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:45.810 --> 35:47.354
[grunts]

35:47.354 --> 35:52.317
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:55.820 --> 35:57.364
‐ Oh, [bleep].

35:57.364 --> 36:01.034
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:01.034 --> 36:03.161
All right, Jason,
let's talk about your

36:03.161 --> 36:04.579
spiked mace here.

36:04.579 --> 36:07.332
Your handle construction
fits in my hand nicely.

36:07.332 --> 36:08.875
It is cylindrical handle,

36:08.875 --> 36:11.169
but it's nice enough
to where I can hold onto it.

36:11.169 --> 36:12.295
There's a good grip to that.

36:12.295 --> 36:14.547
Now, this thing, like you said,

36:14.547 --> 36:16.383
is a murder weapon.

36:16.383 --> 36:21.054
It crushes with every strike,
but in so doing,

36:21.054 --> 36:22.555
some of the spikes came off.

36:22.555 --> 36:24.766
There's about five pieces
missing on this.

36:24.766 --> 36:26.935
But overall, sir,
without a doubt,

36:26.935 --> 36:28.436
and a big headache,

36:28.436 --> 36:29.729
it will KEAL.

36:29.729 --> 36:31.856
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:31.856 --> 36:33.066
All right, Sam,
it's your turn.

36:33.066 --> 36:34.359
You ready?
‐ Yes.

36:34.359 --> 36:35.527
‐ Let's do this.

36:35.527 --> 36:37.821
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:37.821 --> 36:40.323
<i>‐ Jason's mace performed great</i>
<i>in the test.</i>

36:40.323 --> 36:42.075
<i>However, it did lose</i>
<i>some spikes,</i>

36:42.075 --> 36:44.452
<i>so I'm hoping mine doesn't.</i>

36:44.452 --> 36:47.205
I cannot wait to see my mace
go through this dummy.

36:47.205 --> 36:49.582
<i>It's gonna be awesome.</i>

36:49.582 --> 36:56.756
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:58.675 --> 37:01.094
‐ [grunting]

37:01.094 --> 37:08.226
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:11.730 --> 37:14.607
<i>[tense music]</i>

37:14.607 --> 37:18.236
All right, Sam, let's talk
about your spiked mace here.

37:18.236 --> 37:20.447
First up, it's a crusher.

37:20.447 --> 37:22.449
It's a heavy‐forward weapon

37:22.449 --> 37:24.242
that when you're thrusting
with it,

37:24.242 --> 37:26.286
it does penetrate easily.

37:26.286 --> 37:28.538
Now, there's an issue here.

37:28.538 --> 37:30.457
Your handle.

37:30.457 --> 37:31.916
It gets in the way.

37:31.916 --> 37:34.836
Especially with a very
forward‐heavy weapon,

37:34.836 --> 37:37.255
it could potentially hurt
the person wielding it,

37:37.255 --> 37:39.215
which unfortunately
prevents it from being

37:39.215 --> 37:41.092
a fully‐functional weapon.

37:41.092 --> 37:43.178
But despite that,

37:43.178 --> 37:44.637
this is a sharp weapon.

37:44.637 --> 37:48.057
This definitely is something
that will crush, and...

37:48.057 --> 37:49.142
it will KEAL.

37:51.102 --> 37:54.314
<i>[rock music]</i>

37:54.314 --> 37:55.774
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:55.774 --> 37:57.317
‐ Bladesmiths,
welcome to our strength test.

37:57.317 --> 37:58.526
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:58.526 --> 38:00.153
I'm gonna take your weapons,

38:00.153 --> 38:01.780
and I'm gonna play a little
terracotta baseball.

38:01.780 --> 38:03.156
Two things to remember:

38:03.156 --> 38:04.908
<i>it's not what your weapon does</i>

38:04.908 --> 38:05.992
<i>to the jars.</i>

38:05.992 --> 38:07.160
I want to see what the jars

38:07.160 --> 38:08.787
are gonna do to your weapons.

38:08.787 --> 38:09.996
And number two,

38:09.996 --> 38:12.999
I'm gonna be swinging
for the fences.

38:12.999 --> 38:14.876
Jason, you're up.
You ready?

38:14.876 --> 38:16.544
‐ Let's do it.
‐ Let's go.

38:16.544 --> 38:19.005
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

38:19.005 --> 38:20.882
<i>‐ I lost spikes against</i>
<i>the ballistics dummy,</i>

38:20.882 --> 38:22.675
<i>and that's nothing compared</i>
<i>to the hardness</i>

38:22.675 --> 38:24.010
in a terracotta pot.

38:24.010 --> 38:26.012
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:26.012 --> 38:27.972
I'm viably worried
for the structural soundness

38:27.972 --> 38:29.516
<i>of my mace.</i>

38:29.516 --> 38:30.934
<i>If I lose any more spikes,</i>

38:30.934 --> 38:33.520
I think my mace
is gonna be done.

38:35.146 --> 38:38.149
<i>♪ [heavy rock m]</i>

38:38.149 --> 38:45.323
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:56.960 --> 38:59.128
<i>[tense music]</i>

38:59.128 --> 39:00.588
‐ You see on your head,

39:00.588 --> 39:02.382
you've got some of these nubs

39:02.382 --> 39:04.133
that have clay in them‐‐

39:04.133 --> 39:05.301
some that don't.

39:05.301 --> 39:08.012
The ones that don't broke
on the pots,

39:08.012 --> 39:09.681
so you lost a few more spikes.

39:09.681 --> 39:12.433
That being said, though,
it's comfortable.

39:12.433 --> 39:15.562
I can keep swinging this weapon
for quite a while/

39:15.562 --> 39:17.856
Even if more spikes came off,

39:17.856 --> 39:19.774
this is still a deadly weapon

39:19.774 --> 39:21.526
'cause you got the ball on here
with the nubs

39:21.526 --> 39:22.694
and your main spike.

39:22.694 --> 39:25.363
Overall, good job.

39:25.363 --> 39:26.406
Hey, Sam.

39:26.406 --> 39:28.074
‐ Hey.
‐ You ready?

39:28.074 --> 39:29.200
‐ Oh, yeah.
‐ Okay.

39:29.200 --> 39:32.036
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:32.036 --> 39:33.830
<i>‐ I think my spikes</i>
<i>are gonna hold up,</i>

39:33.830 --> 39:36.207
<i>but I'm really concerned</i>
<i>about my handle.</i>

39:36.207 --> 39:37.667
It's already hurt Doug.

39:37.667 --> 39:39.043
<i>I don't want any more</i>
<i>of the judges</i>

39:39.043 --> 39:40.378
<i>to hurt themselves.</i>

39:40.378 --> 39:41.546
See what happens.

39:41.546 --> 39:44.549
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

39:44.549 --> 39:47.385
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:07.405 --> 40:10.241
<i>[somber music]</i>

40:10.241 --> 40:13.077
‐ Sam, in the world of weapons
and warriors,

40:13.077 --> 40:15.371
a weapon should be feared
by your enemy‐‐

40:15.371 --> 40:17.665
not by the warrior
who wields it.

40:17.665 --> 40:19.876
<i>Because the pommel</i>
<i>is so out of scale</i>

40:19.876 --> 40:22.253
and inflicted so much harm
to Doug

40:22.253 --> 40:23.838
in that first KEAL test

40:23.838 --> 40:25.423
in the strength test,

40:25.423 --> 40:27.592
we just can't take the risk

40:27.592 --> 40:28.927
of injuring one of our judges.

40:28.927 --> 40:30.762
And for that reason,

40:30.762 --> 40:32.931
I'd like to invite you
to shake our hands,

40:32.931 --> 40:34.766
shake your competitor's hand,

40:34.766 --> 40:36.643
and then please
leave The Forge.

40:36.643 --> 40:39.020
<i>[rock music]</i>

40:39.020 --> 40:41.606
It looks fantastic, man.

40:41.606 --> 40:44.817
‐ I'm not surprised
at the judges' ruling.

40:44.817 --> 40:46.361
<i>I totally agree</i>
<i>with what they said.</i>

40:46.361 --> 40:48.947
I may not be
the "Forged in Fire" champion,

40:48.947 --> 40:50.782
but I got to use
the power hammer

40:50.782 --> 40:53.993
<i>and I got to make an excellent</i>
<i>blade and cool mace,</i>

40:53.993 --> 40:55.620
so I'm really happy.

40:55.620 --> 40:58.957
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:58.957 --> 41:01.709
‐ Jason, your weapon
has elevated you

41:01.709 --> 41:04.253
to the title
of "Forged in Fire" champion,

41:04.253 --> 41:06.422
and you'll be receiving a check
for $10,000.

41:06.422 --> 41:07.548
Good job, brother.

41:07.548 --> 41:10.718
[applause]

41:11.469 --> 41:12.512
[chuckling]

41:12.512 --> 41:14.138
Uh, I'm absolutely astounded.

41:14.138 --> 41:15.098
I won.

41:15.098 --> 41:17.308
<i>I feel very, very lucky</i>

41:17.308 --> 41:18.476
<i>and so very thankful.</i>

41:18.476 --> 41:19.852
Being the "Forged in Fire"
champion

41:19.852 --> 41:21.813
means that it validates
my skills.

41:21.813 --> 41:24.691
<i>And I'm able to look</i>
<i>at my children and I can say,</i>

41:24.691 --> 41:26.818
"Follow your dreams.
Chase 'em.

41:26.818 --> 41:28.653
You can achieve anything."

41:28.653 --> 41:34.784
<i>♪ ♪</i>
